:12pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:5pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.22pt; padding-left:3.68pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Impact on food production of severe deposition of volcanic ash across the UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Â  </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:5pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 67.22pt; padding-left:3.68pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Extreme consumer behaviour and severely altered buying patterns (for reasons possibly</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> not connected to food supply)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ul><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Food security incidents can happen at any stage in the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">food supply chain; occurring during primary production, distribution, processing, storage and retail. As food businesses respond to changing demand, economic pressures create requirements for cheaper sourcing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> leading to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> changes in the pattern of imports</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> an</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">d the vulnerabilities associated with them.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="25" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Tackling problems with imported foods requires a combination of approaches: continued vigilance at border controls, intelligence-based target</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> surveillance, promoting food safety in developing countries and raising awareness of existing EU food safety legislation. </span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Food imports from outside the EU are subject to controls which are different between animal and non-animal products. Animal product</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s may only be imported through designated Border Inspection Points (there are around 20 in the UK). At the posts the product is subject to documentary and physical checks. Non-animal products may be imported through around 80 seaports and airports around t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he UK. Documentary checks are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">conducted and a small proportion of products will be subject to additional checks or sampling.Â  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="27" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Underpinning all this activity is co-operation nationally and internationally to ensure that risks are identified and managed. K</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ey to this is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> sharing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">information and intelligence, based on building trust and partnerships.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="28" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The FSA plays an active role in the work of the European Food Safety Authority and there are active links and regular exchanges of information with intern</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ational food safety authorities in other </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">countries such as the USA, Canada, Australia and New Zealand. The FSA is also working with EFSA and the European Commission to improve links with other countries beyond the EU.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">V</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">alue and contribution of science </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">and GM</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> technology to UK food security</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="29" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Global food security drivers and challenges have the potential to impact on FSA relevant policy and delivery issues â€“ presenting both challenges and opportunities. The science and evidence gathering that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">FSA funds</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> implicitly reflects the changing environment of a global food supply system. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="30" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hanges in global food production</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are likely to raise the question of t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he use of GM products in the UK as the world</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> need</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to produce more food usin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">g less land, water, fertilise</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">r and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">energy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The FSA is responsible for safety assessment of food and feed derived from genetically modified organisms (GMOs) in the UK. The use of GM materials is controlled by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Regulation (EC) 1829/2003 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which stipulates that GM foods may only be authoriz</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ed for sale in the EU if they are judged not to present a risk to health, not to mislead consumers and not to be of less nutritional value than the foods they are intended to replace</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="31" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Authorisation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the food and feed use</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of GM crops takes place at a Eur</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">opean level. The European Food Safety Authority (EFSA), in consultation with the appropriate competent authority, is required to provide a risk assessment. This assessment includes a detailed consideration of the potential for toxic, nutritional and allerg</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">enic effects. The final decision on authorisation is taken by Member States at the Standing Committee on Animal Health and the Food Chain. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="32" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The FSA monitors </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the food sector for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">new and emerging technologies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that are being </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">dev</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">eloped, f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">or example the use of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nanomaterial</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in food packaging to slow decay rates</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> high throughput sampling of products to detect food safety hazards</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t is vital </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that we</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> ensure such new </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">technologies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> have a proven ability to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> enhance food safety</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> as these new technologies have the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">potential</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to increase resilience in the food chain.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="33" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">FSA are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">involved in collaborative work, to identify possible risks before they emerge. We are partners in sponsoring the Centre for Environmental Risk and Futures (CERF) at Cranfield University.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> The centre provides horizon scanning and futures studies across the food and environment areas, to help identify and address potential new threats and opportunities, to deliver safer food in the long-term. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Centre provides </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">FSA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> with access to expert</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ise we do not have at the Agency, allowing us to share costs and to develop a common understanding of cross-cutting issues by working in partnership with OGDs.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How food and farming supply chains, and the current systems for traceability can contribute to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">increased resilience</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="34" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> ever increasing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">global </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">demand for food coupled with an increasing global population and increased demand from developing countries has encouraged innovation and diversification in food production, including the globalisation of fo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">od supply and the development of an increasingly complex and multi-layered supply chain.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="35" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">FSA recognise</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">robust traceability systems are critical to maintaining the integrity of the supply chain and to support crisis management activities. </span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">As seen during the horsemeat incident, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">supply chains can be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> highly complex and lengthy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> can lead to increased challenges for food busin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">esses in maintaining standards.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="37" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.68pt; padding-left:14.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Working in partnership with industry the FSA encouraged the introduction of food au</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">thenticity </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">testing by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">food businesses</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, which i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n combination </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">withÂ  technological improvements in traceability of food from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">â€˜</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">farm to fork</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">â€™</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">should </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">increase resilience to food fraudÂ  and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">provide reassurance </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to consumers.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">December </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Details of the review can be accessed at </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/professor-chris-elliott-to-lead-review-into-food-supply-networks"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/govern</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">ment/news/professor-chris-elliott-to-lead-review-into-food-supply-networks</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Further information can be accessed from the GFS website at </span><a href="http://www.foodsecurity.ac.uk/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.foodsecurity.ac.uk/</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p 